The 61-year-old President has not appeared in public for nearly two weeks, raising speculation on his whereabouts.President Magufuli, while addressing mourners at Ambassador Kijazi’s burial, advised Tanzanians to take precautions against the Covid-19 pandemic. The Government of Kenya remained uncharacteristically tight-lipped about the reported presence of Tanzanian President John Pombe Magufuli at one of Nairobi’s top private hospitals for treatment. 

There was presidential level security in Nairobi Hospital’s VIP North Wing and access to the premier hospital’s presidential suites was more severe than usual. 



