The Church did not specify the actual diseases the priests suffered from. 

But Gervas Nyaisonga, the President of the Tanzanian Episcopoal Conference, the highest organ of the church in the country, distributed guidelines to bishops of various dioceses on measures to protect themselves against Covid-19 while presiding over religious services. 






The World Health Organisation has also repeatedly pressed Tanzania to disclose its Covid-19 infection numbers and issue public health measures against the deadly virus. 

Reporting by Washington Gikunju, Vincent Achuka, Aggrey Mutambo and Nasibo Kabale This comes amid reports that death has robbed the country of at least 10 prominent persons. Tanzanian president has long played down the virus and in mid-2020 said prayer had rid Tanzania of Covid-19 and no-one in his country needed masks. The President has also announced that funerals will take place within 72 hours. In just 12 months, the number of the dead has swelled – now heading towards 1,900 in Kenya.